

= Bio  =

I'm a sociologist, teacher and&nbsp;electronic artist. In 2001 I was one of the founding members of the Milan-based experimental collective [Http://www.otolab.net otolab] with whom I investigate visual dramaturgic representation of sound.&nbsp;I teach theories, methodologies and tecniques of the audiovisual performance at NABA&nbsp;in Milan and in several other seminars and courses around Italy. I hold a PhD in Urban European Studies at the University of Miano-Bicocca; my research in urban sociology investigates the relationships among city, creative economy and social innovation processes, with a special focus on underground artists co-optation in mainstream markets. Now I'm a post-doc researcher at the University of Milan and I work on the EU funded project [http://www.edufashion.org/ EDUfashion] and its community [http://openwear.org/ Openwear], dealing with: P2P economies; crowdsourcing; desktop and distributed manufacturing; clothing; and fashion.

